body.name: BreathableBaby Breathable Mesh Liner for Full-Size Cribs, Classic 3mm Mesh, Owl Fun Gray (Size 4FS Covers 3 or 4 Sides)
deliveryMessages: Or fastest delivery Friday, February 16. Order within 6 hrs 39 mins
features: 3MM CLASSIC MESH WITH 85% LIGHT BLOCKING RATING: Constructed from 3 mm mesh with A.C.T. Air Channel Technology for unrestricted airflow. 100% polyester. 1" (2.54 cm) trim on top and bottom. Machine washable.

FITS FULL-SIZE STYLES WITH A 52" x 28" (132 CM x 71 CM) MATTRESS: Install long 11" x 111" (28 cm x 282 cm) and short 11" x 82" (28 cm x 208 cm) panels to cover 4 sides or only the long panel to cover 3 sides. Do not use on solid end styles or mini cribs.

SAFETY TESTED & TRUSTED: From BreathableBaby, the original breathable mesh liner with millions sold since 2002. Independently tested for safety to comply with ASTM F1917 for infant bedding. Contains no added chemicals, flame retardants or formaldehyde.

HELPS KEEP ARMS AND LEGS SAFELY INSIDE WITHOUT THE RISK OF RESTRICTED AIRFLOW: A single layer of breathable mesh allows exhaled air to pass through the fabric and mitigates risks associated with padded "crib bumpers" (banned in the US in 2022).

EASY TO INSTALL: Adjusts to fit with hook and loop. Tuck the bottom fabric trim below the top edge of the mattress and secure all fastenings before use. Review instruction manual and installation video or contact customer care for assistance.
body.description: At BreathableBaby, safety is first, last, and everything in between. That's why we have invested countless hours into medical and scientific research to make our products safer. We invented and perfected the breathable mesh liner. The original breathable mesh liner with millions sold since 2002.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 24, 2014
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars An Excellent, Safer Option
reviews.reviewText: We just put this Breathable Baby bumper on our crib (the gray chevron print with navy blue trim), though baby-to-be won't actually be here for another couple of months.It does look exactly as it does in the Amazon-provided photos. HOWEVER, one thing that is not super obvious in the pictures, is that the chevron print is ONLY on the inside of the crib bumper; the side facing out is solid gray. I was a teeny bit disappointed in this, although it's not a 'deal breaker' because I understand this is more of a safety item, and won't be used for very long either. I did think it was worth noting in my review though!The bumper comes in two solid pieces, and if you look carefully at the pictures, you can see that it stays put with velcro tabs, by sort of threading through slats and then folding back and sticking to itself. It seemed a bit confusing at first, but the instructions that come in the package are excellent, and provide clear diagrams for various types of cribs - solid back, solid sides, and slats all the way aroun (we have slats on all sides). The breathable mesh fabric does definitely seem like it is truly breathable, and a much safer option for once your child starts to roll - if they were to roll over and get tangled up in the bumper at all, I'd greatly prefer this one over a traditional bumper, and not having one at all makes me a little nervous with the slats.While we do like and recommend this bumper, the one downfall is the way this bumper threads through the corner posts. There is a small pocket created at each corner, because it doesn't fold flush around them (there is no way for it to); instead, it creates a triangle, with the bumper at a diagonal in front of the corner posts, and the 'L' of the posts behind it. From what I understand, most children who begin to roll and explore their crib are generally going to the front or back sides, not the corners. But if our kiddo does ever find his way to that corner, I'll be concerned that he can somehow get tangled up underneath/behind there, and because of this, as SOON as he can sit up or pull himself up even slightly, the bumper will come off.Overall, we think this is the safest bumper option available if you're going to go with one, and we also think it appears well-made and attractive, so we recommend it. We'll have to see how it holds up once baby is here, so I will come back and review this in several months.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 10, 2018
reviews.reviewText: We couldn’t be happier with this liner. We didn’t transition our daughter to her crib from her halo bassinest until after 6 months. Once we did, she seemed to get a hand or foot between the slats often. Our nursery has gray walls, a white crib, and pink accents so I ordered this hoping for a pleasant match. Sometimes the colors in these online products can be off putting when you see it in person. Not the case here! It is a perfect match. The gray is a beautiful true gray, the pink is soft and beautiful, and the white is perfect. This also isn’t an old school bumper that you just tie off to the slats. It’s a two piece bumper. You place the longer piece against the back of the crib and follow the directions to thread through in certain places then secure with very strong Velcro and finish off with ties. The second piece is shorter and goes along the front in a similar fashion. It leaves no gaps and my little one hasn’t had any more slips between the slats. I was a little intimidated when I originally removed it from the package because their were no directions included but the company directs you to their website where there is a great video tutorial (which is a big plus for mommy brain!). I’ve washed the liner once and it held up great. We use it with the Graco Rory convertible crib and it’s a perfect fit. I don’t worry that my daughter will step on the liner and use it as leverage to step out of the crib. The liner slides down from the top if she tries to step on it but it still maintains a barrier from allowing her feet and hands to slide out. She likes to pull it down a little bit to peak out when she should be sleeping! She also loves the animals printed around bumper. They are beautiful and friendly looking and she loves laying in bed and cooing to the animals! If you found this review helpful, please click the helpful button 😉
